Sentencas: MnCu (Mn:Cu = 1:1, atomic ratio) metallic coatings have been deposited by magnetron sputtering on bare and on 100 h pre-oxidized SUS 430 steel for planar solid oxide fuel cells interconnects application.
Titulo: Sputtered MnCu metallic coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects application

Sentencas: After oxidation at 800 degrees C in air, the MnCu coating directly deposited on the bare steel has been thermally converted to (Mn,Cu)(3)O-4 spinel with Fe, containing discrete CuO on the outer surface.
Titulo: Sputtered MnCu metallic coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects application

Sentencas: Nevertheless, the converted (Mn,Cu)(3)O-4/CuO layer from the MnCu coating deposited on the pre-oxidized steelis almost free of Fe.
Titulo: Sputtered MnCu metallic coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects application

Sentencas: A double-layer oxide structure with a main (Mn,Cu)(3)O-4 spinel layer atop a Cr-rich oxide layer has been developed on the bare and pre-oxidized steel samples with MnCu coatings after thermal exposure.
Titulo: Sputtered MnCu metallic coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects application

Sentencas: The outer layer mainly consisted of (Mn,Cu)(3)O-4 spinel has not only significantly suppressed Cr outward migration to the scale surface, but also effectively reduced the area specific resistance (ASR) of the scale.
Titulo: Sputtered MnCu metallic coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects application

Sentencas: The sputtered MnCu metallic coating is a very promising candidate for steel interconnect coating material.
Titulo: Sputtered MnCu metallic coating on ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects application
